<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of Simplicia species and showing locations discussed in text." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.75.10328.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/114287" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">1</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zotov, New Zealand J. Bot. 9: 542" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Zotov" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia buchananii" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchananii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia buchananii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to North-West Nelson, South Island.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="130" type="recognition">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Recognition.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zotov, New Zealand J. Bot. 9: 542" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Zotov" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia buchananii" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchananii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia buchananii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirk, T. N. Z. I. 29: 497, t. 44" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia laxa" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Lange, J. R. Rolfe, Smissen &amp; Ogle" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia felix" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the tufted growth habit, erect culms, and by the linear inflorescences, whose branches are usually tightly appressed to the rachises (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Simplicia buchananii. A habitat, Kahurangi National Park, North West Nelson, South Island, New Zealand B growth habit and inflorescence C culm, leaf base, sheath and ligule D spikelet showing reduced glumes and lemma (images: J. R. Rolfe)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.75.10328.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/114295" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">5</figureCitation>
, for other differences see Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Sample details." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D40CB6DD4E7A147F8595137B2BC2306B" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" tableUuid="D40CB6DD4E7A147F8595137B2BC2306B">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="130" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zotov, New Zealand J. Bot. 9: 542" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Zotov" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia buchananii" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchananii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia buchananii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a biologically sparse species of calcareous rock habitats (including shaded rock outcrops, boulderfalls, rock overhangs and cave entrances) within montane forest (
<bibRefCitation author="de Lange, P" journalOrPublisher="Canterbury University Press, Christchurch" pageId="20" pageNumber="139" refId="B4" refString="de Lange, P, Heenan, P, Norton, D, Rolfe, J, Sawyer, J, 2010. Threatened plants of New Zealand. Canterbury University Press, Christchurch" title="Threatened plants of New Zealand" year="2010">de Lange et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="130" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="130">
Using the New Zealand Threat Classification System (
<bibRefCitation author="Townsend, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Department of Conservation, Wellington" pageId="21" pageNumber="140" publicationUrl="http://www.doc.govt.nz/Documents/science-and-technical/sap244.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Townsend, AJ, de Lange, PJ, Norton, DA, Molloy, J, Miskelly, C, Duffy, C, 2008. New Zealand Threat Classification manual. Department of Conservation, Wellington, http://www.doc.govt.nz/Documents/science-and-technical/sap244.pdf" title="New Zealand Threat Classification manual" url="http://www.doc.govt.nz/Documents/science-and-technical/sap244.pdf" year="2008">Townsend et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zotov, New Zealand J. Bot. 9: 542" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Zotov" class="Insecta" family="Gramineae" genus="Simplicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Simplicia buchananii" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchananii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="130">Simplicia buchananii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been assessed as 'Threatened / Nationally 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Critical’">Critical'</normalizedToken>
with the qualifiers 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘DP’">'DP'</normalizedToken>
[Data Poor], 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘RR’">'RR'</normalizedToken>
[Range Restricted] and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Sp’">'Sp'</normalizedToken>
[Sparse] (de Lange et al. 2013). The threats this species faces were summarised by 
<bibRefCitation author="de Lange, P" journalOrPublisher="Canterbury University Press, Christchurch" pageId="20" pageNumber="139" refId="B4" refString="de Lange, P, Heenan, P, Norton, D, Rolfe, J, Sawyer, J, 2010. Threatened plants of New Zealand. Canterbury University Press, Christchurch" title="Threatened plants of New Zealand" year="2010">de Lange et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/0028825X.2010.525244" author="Smissen, RD" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Journal of Botany" pageId="21" pageNumber="140" pagination="187 - 199" refId="B17" refString="Smissen, RD, de Lange, PJ, Thorsen, MJ, Ogle, CC, 2011. Species delimitation and genetic variation in the rare New Zealand endemic grass Simplicia. New Zealand Journal of Botany 49: 187 - 199, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/0028825X.2010.525244" title="Species delimitation and genetic variation in the rare New Zealand endemic grass Simplicia." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/0028825X.2010.525244" volume="49" year="2011">Smissen et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on our current knowledge of this species the current threat status remains appropriate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
